<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-09-22T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-09-22T15:36:00-05:00" n="1087" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/1402</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Parker</persName>,
                                representing American interests, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                    of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-09-22T14:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 22, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>415. Department’s 423, September 18, 6 p.m. Decree dated June 19, 1915,
                            provides: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Taxes paid to pretended authorities before occupation by
                                    Constitutionalist forces are considered paid. Rear taxes should
                                    be paid within a month from occupation thereafter with
                                    penalties. If taxes should have been paid in advance they must
                                    be repaid.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>Nevertheless I am making investigation for a more recent decree relating
                            thereto.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Parker</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>